From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 21:00:00 +0000
Subject: ufs: rockchip: rk3576: Hard-reset controller on init to clear vendor
 SPL handoff state

When a vendor (Rockchip rkbin) SPL hands off to U-Boot proper, the UFS
host controller is left in an active state from the SPL's link-startup
and device discovery. The mainline ufshcd-rockchip driver's normal HCE
toggle (Host Controller Enable bit) does not fully clear that state on
RK3576: subsequent UIC commands time out with "Controller not ready to
accept UIC commands", and the bus rescan loops indefinitely.

Pulse the controller's reset-controller bulk (the four SRST_*_UFS_*
resets already requested by ufs_rockchip_common_init) at the start of
the SoC-specific init hook. This clears the controller register state
fully -- equivalent to a SoC-level reset of the UFS block -- so the
subsequent HCE enable, link startup, and SCSI scan all proceed cleanly.

Has no effect when SPL is the mainline-built one (controller comes up
already-fresh in SPL), and is a no-op for boards without UFS-capable
boot ROMs.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/ufs/ufs-rockchip.c | 22 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/ufs/ufs-rockchip.c b/drivers/ufs/ufs-rockchip.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/ufs/ufs-rockchip.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/ufs-rockchip.c
@@ -180,6 +180,7 @@ static int ufs_rockchip_device_reset(struct ufs_hba *hba)
 
 static int ufs_rockchip_rk3576_init(struct ufs_hba *hba)
 {
+	struct ufs_rockchip_host *host;
 	int ret = 0;
 
 	ret = ufs_rockchip_common_init(hba);
@@ -188,6 +189,27 @@ static int ufs_rockchip_rk3576_init(struct ufs_hba *hba)
 		return ret;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * Hard-reset the UFS controller through the reset-controller framework.
+	 * Vendor (rkbin) SPL leaves the controller in a state where the normal
+	 * HCE toggle is insufficient — UIC commands time out with "Controller
+	 * not ready". Pulsing SRST_A_UFS_BIU/SYS/UFS/P_UFS_GRF clears all
+	 * controller registers, so the regular ufshcd_init flow can proceed.
+	 */
+	host = dev_get_priv(hba->dev);
+	ret = reset_assert_bulk(&host->rsts);
+	if (ret) {
+		dev_err(hba->dev, "%s: reset assert fail %d\n", __func__, ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+	udelay(100);
+	ret = reset_deassert_bulk(&host->rsts);
+	if (ret) {
+		dev_err(hba->dev, "%s: reset deassert fail %d\n", __func__, ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+	udelay(100);
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
